SUMMARY:Narrativizing a Moment: A Guided Writing Workshop NEW
DESCRIPTION:This is a paid Adult School class. Click here to register on 
 the Adult School website.\n\nThrough a series of guided writing prompts\, 
 you will be encouraged to write your experiences and learn storytelling 
 techniques that will aid in your ability to access\, write\, and put shape 
 to your personal memories. No formal writing training/experience needed! 
 Come with an open mind and willingness to be vulnerable. (Note: please be 
 prepared to write - either with pen and paper or typing on a computer\, 
 whatever you're more comfortable with!)\n\nThis class is offered in 
 partnership with the Asian American Writers Workshop.
LOCATION:Montclair Main - Classroom\, Montclair Public Library
ORGANIZER;CN="Montclair Adult School":MAILTO:adultschool@montclairlibrary.org
CATEGORIES:Adult School, Writing
UID:LibCal-10306-15415559
URL:https://bccls.libcal.com/event/15415559
