SUMMARY:(POSTPONED) Practical Spanish 1
DESCRIPTION:NEW DATE TBA DUE TO WEATHER\n\n \n\nThis is a paid Adult School 
 class. Click here to register. \n\nThis class is for those of you who know 
 little to no Spanish and are interested in acquiring some practical 
 communication skills. You will be introduced to basic greetings and 
 practice useful questions and answers. You will learn the fundamentals of 
 Spanish pronunciation while mastering introductory grammar and 
 vocabulary.\n\nTopics 
 covered:\n\n\n	conversation/questions\n	greetings\n	personal 
 information\n	expressions of courtesy\n	feelings\n	asking for 
 direction\n	talk about needs and want\n	where people are 
 from.\n	Alphabet\n	Numbers/Days/date\n	Colors\n	Basic commands\n	Some 
 ar/er/ir  regular verbs\n	Verb to be: ser/estar\n	Verb to go: ir\n	Verb 
 Tener/Necesitar/Querer\n	Ir   a\n	Negation\n	Subject pronouns/difference 
 between Tú/Usted\n	Gender and number of nouns/definite/indefinite 
 articles\n	Some adjectives including cuánto/a\n	The expression 
 “Hay”\n	Basic geography\, culture and food.\n\n\nSkip date: No class on 
 February 16\, 2026
LOCATION:Montclair Main - Classroom\, Montclair Public Library
ORGANIZER;CN="Montclair Adult School":MAILTO:adultschool@montclairlibrary.org
CATEGORIES:Adult School, Language
