SUMMARY:Writing: Method and Motivation (MOVED ONLINE)
DESCRIPTION:Today's session of this class was moved online due to concerns 
 over weather conditions. It is scheduled return to an in-person class for 
 future sessions.\n\nThis is a paid Adult School class. Click here to 
 register.\n\nA workshop for anyone who wants to write\, or wants to infuse 
 their existing writing practice with new energy. In each class\, we'll 
 consider one element of fiction or creative non-fiction\, such as point of 
 view\, narrative voice\, and what makes a piece of writing riveting\, or 
 boring. Students can expect in-class writing prompts\, reading aloud\, and 
 optional homework. Positive encouragement\, rather than formal critiques\,  
 will be featured\, and inspiration and organization for writers will be 
 discussed. Students should bring whatever they use to write to each class.
LOCATION:Montclair Main - Conference Room\, Montclair Public Library
ORGANIZER;CN="Montclair Adult School":MAILTO:adultschool@montclairlibrary.org
CATEGORIES:Adult School
