SUMMARY:Skype a Scientist! (Ages 8 - 18)
DESCRIPTION:Join us for a virtual q a session with Julia McDonough\, a PhD 
 student studying Applied Biology at UMass Lowell! Her research focuses on 
 the impact of climate change on oysters.\nPlease have your questions 
 prepared ahead of the Zoom. You can email them to us here.\nRegister now -- 
 you must sign up here to gain access.\n\nMeet your presenter:\n\nJulia 
 McDonough is a 3rd year PhD student at the University of Massachusetts 
 Lowell. The lab she work in studies how climate change and disease affect 
 marine organisms. They use a combination of fieldwork\, lab work\, and 
 bioinformatics to study changes in these organisms. Her research focuses on 
 oysters and how they adapt and respond to environmental stressors\, like 
 warming temperatures and deoxygenated water\, by looking at their genes. 
 Through her work\, she aims to better understand the impacts of climate 
 change on coastal ecosystems and the organisms that support them.\n\nSign 
 up for the Monthly Teen Newsletter
LOCATION:Montclair Public Library
ORGANIZER;CN="Montclair Library":MAILTO:events@montclairlibrary.org
CATEGORIES:Children's Programs, STEM / STEAM, Teen Services
