SUMMARY:Everything Book Club\, "Giovanni's Room" by James Baldwin
DESCRIPTION:Don't miss the Library's Open Book / Open Mind program with 
 author Nicholas Boggs about his bestselling new biography "Baldwin: A Love 
 Story" on Sunday\, March 8\, two days before book club!  In our 
 discussion\, we'll talk about Boggs's conversation as well as Baldwin's 
 brilliant classic about a young American expat caught between conventional 
 morality and his true desires in 1950s Paris. If you've always meant to 
 read this book\, now's your chance! If you've read it before\, let's 
 explore it again together in the context of Baldwin's own life. 
 \n\n“Exciting…. A book that belongs in the top rank of fiction.” 
 —The Atlantic\n\nJames Baldwin was an essayist\, playwright\, novelist 
 and voice of the American civil rights movement known for works including 
 'Notes of a Native Son\,' 'The Fire Next Time' and 'Go Tell It on the 
 Mountain.'
LOCATION:Montclair Main - Tower Room\, Montclair Public Library
ORGANIZER;CN="Montclair Library":MAILTO:events@montclairlibrary.org
CATEGORIES:Book Discussion
