SUMMARY:Author Chat - "Give Her Credit" - With Grace Williams NEW
DESCRIPTION:This is a free Adult School class. Registration is required. 
 Click here to register.\n\nDid you know that women in the mid-1970s still 
 could not get a credit card\, a mortgage or a business loan without a male 
 co-signer? Have you ever wondered just how this sorry state of affairs came 
 to change?  Join us for a conversation between Grace Williams\, financial 
 reporter\, podcast co-host\, and author of "Give Her Credit: The Untold 
 Account of a Women's Bank That Empowered a Generation\," and Eleanor Galt 
 Lin\, a certified financial planner and advisory at Merrill Lynch\, to 
 learn more about a remarkable group of women in Denver who disrupted the 
 1970s male-run world of business\, banking\, and finance--and made history.
LOCATION:Montclair Main - Conference Room\, Montclair Public Library
ORGANIZER;CN="Montclair Adult School":MAILTO:adultschool@montclairlibrary.org
CATEGORIES:Adult School
UID:LibCal-10306-15658407
URL:https://bccls.libcal.com/event/15658407
