SUMMARY:A History of the Cherry Orchards of Branch Brook Park
DESCRIPTION:This is a free Adult School class. Registration is required. 
 Click here to register.\n\nWhile the famous Cherry Blossom Trees have 
 graced Branch Brook Park since 1927\, an official festival took another 50 
 years.  First celebrated in 1976\, the Cherry Blossom Festival in Newark's 
 Branch Brook Park has become an annual event\, bringing hundreds of 
 thousands of visitors to the Park. \n\nDuring this talk\, we'll discuss why 
 there are Cherry Blossom Trees in Branch Brook Park\, the meaning behind 
 them\, and the history of the Festivals that have taken place.\n\nFind out 
 about their origins in 1927 and the creation of the Cherry Blossom Festival 
 in Branch Brook Park from Maressa MacFarlane\, archivist of the Essex 
 County Park System.
LOCATION:Montclair Main - Auditorium
ORGANIZER;CN="Montclair Library":MAILTO:events@montclairlibrary.org
CATEGORIES:Adult School
UID:LibCal-10306-15580368
URL:https://bccls.libcal.com/event/15580368
