DTEND:20260324T233000Z
DTSTAMP:20260324T000000Z
SUMMARY:Pysanky: The Ancient Art of Egg Decorating
DESCRIPTION:This is a paid Adult School class. Click here to 
 register.\n\nPysanky–the art of creating decorative eggs–is a 
 traditional Ukrainian folk art form that is thousands of years old. In this 
 class\, you will learn about the historical significance of this delicate 
 art form\, designs and techniques\, and finally create an egg of your own 
 using beeswax and dyes that are applied in layers.\n\nThis meditative and 
 communal experience is unlike any other art process and for many this 
 workshop marks the beginning of a spring time family tradition that can be 
 passed on and enjoyed for years to come.\n\nNo experience is required to 
 participate in this workshop. Participants will be provided with all 
 materials\, and leave with a beautiful egg of their own creation!
LOCATION:Montclair Main - Auditorium\, Montclair Public Library
ORGANIZER;CN="Montclair Adult School":MAILTO:adultschool@montclairlibrary.org
CATEGORIES:Adult School, Arts & Crafts
UID:LibCal-10306-15723867
URL:https://bccls.libcal.com/event/15723867
